## API Boundaries

Two runtime API routes exist at MVP (plus a health check):

| Endpoint | Method | Called from | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| `/combinations.json` | GET (static) | `lib/manifest.ts` | Served from CDN/static host â€” not a server route |
| `/api/feedback` | POST | `FeedbackPrompt` | Returns `{ ok: true }` on success |
| `/health` | GET | Ops / load balancer | Returns `ok` â€” API server liveness |

**Deferred post-launch:** `GET /api/profile/:slug/stats` and a confidence-count hook. Not implemented at MVP.

**There is no `api` module abstraction.** One POST endpoint does not justify a typed wrapper. Calls are made with plain `fetch` at the call site.

**There is no `/api/generate` endpoint at MVP.** Slug construction happens client-side in `CombinationForm`. The slug is deterministic: `[printer]-[material]-[nozzle]-[goal]`. The form validates against the manifest client-side before navigating.

