## What Does NOT Exist at MVP

This is a hard list. If an agent suggests any of the following, it is out of scope.

| Pattern | Why it does not exist |
|---|---|
| `src/features/` | The project uses `src/pages/` â€” approved in `folder-structure.md` |
| `src/hooks/` | No shared hooks yet; manifest and feedback are handled inline |
| `src/store/` | No global store; Zustand is not installed |
| `src/types/` directory | `src/types.ts` is a single file by explicit architectural decision |
| `@tanstack/react-query` | Not installed; plain `fetch` is sufficient at MVP |
| `SlicerOverride.tsx` | Cut at MVP â€” slicer format is derived from printer |
| `Button.tsx` / `Card.tsx` in shared | Not built; CSS utility classes in `global.css` at MVP |
| Storybook | Not in the spec; not in any story |
| `api.ts` per page/feature | One direct `fetch` call does not require an abstraction layer |
| `src/lib/httpClient.ts` | Not needed; plain `fetch` is sufficient |
| `POST /api/generate` | Client-side slug construction replaces it |
| `GET /api/profile/:slug/stats` | Deferred post-launch â€” static confidence message at MVP |
| `forwardRef` | React 19 â€” `ref` is a prop |

